<td width="83%" class="lighttable">
<br />
<font class="post">
<b> Greetings Rallos Zek </b><br>Greetings,<br><br>For those that have any experience in the online game, Meridian59, I have come here to tell you that it is back. So back. After a two year run-in with all kind of pirated servers, the original owners of the game bought the rights back and decided to host a server. Not surprisingly, over 500 people have already registered. If you have any interest in the game, or want to get in touch with some friends, check out some of these sites. <br><br><a href="http://www.gilcon.net/m59forum" target="_blank">http://www.gilcon.net/m59forum</a><br><a href="http://www.neardeathstudios.com" target="_blank">http://www.neardeathstudios.com</a><br><a href="http://www.geocities.com/aloquent/2.html" target="_blank">http://www.geocities.com/aloquent/2.html</a><br><br>Also, for those of you that are not familiar with Meridian59...<br><br>Meridian59 was the first ever MMORPG ever. It was produced in 1996, and since then has been the best ever PVP Game ever. Everquest cannot compete with it in terms of PvP. Although lacking in gameplay, the communication system and the PvP system are a great change if you are looking to take a break from EQ. Anyways, good luck.<br><br>If you have any questions, please email me at <a href="mailto:Aloquent@aol.com">Aloquent@aol.com</a><br><br>Long live Meridian. <br><br>-Jay Griffin<br>  


